1. Jaundice (yellowing of the skin and whites of the eyes)

5. Loss of appetite

While both options include loss of appetite, which is a symptom of chronic cholestasis, frequent headaches are not typically associated with this condition. Therefore, option (b), which only mentions loss of appetite, is more likely to be a symptom experienced by David due to his chronic cholestasis diagnosis.
